      "body": "**T9 (Albanese UP glue): the `Albanese` subproject is materially AHEAD of the AJC copy on the rational-map-extension leg \u2014 port before assembling.** Verified against both working trees (real code sorries, cheat-scanned clean; no `admit`/`native_decide`/`sorryAx`).\n\n- **`Thm32RationalMapExtension.lean`** \u2014 subproject copy is **sorry-free**; the AJC copy still carries **2** real sorries (`IsReduced A.left` at ~155, and ~294). This is `thm:rational_map_to_av_extends`, the key dependency of `descentThroughBirationalSigma`.\n- **`CodimOneExtension.lean`** \u2014 subproject is down to **1** real sorry (`indeterminacy_pure_codim_one_into_grpScheme`, Milne \u00a7I.3 Lemma 3.3, **substep 4b** = codim-1 diagonal-intersection / Hartshorne AG 9.2 bound, ~1721). AJC copy has **3**; the extra two are the smooth\u27f9regular gaps the subproject closed.\n- **Three new sorry-free support files exist only in the subproject**, imported by its `CodimOneExtension`: `Albanese/PolePurity.lean` (pole-divisor purity, Milne 3.3 substep 4a), `Albanese/SmoothPrimeRegularity.lean` (Stacks 00TT at all primes, Serre-free), `Albanese/StandardSmoothDimension.lean` (Stacks 00OE/00ON Krull-dim). Porting them into AJC closes the two extra `CodimOneExtension` sorries and supplies the 3.3 substep-4a input.\n- **`AlbaneseUP.lean` is byte-identical (skeleton) in both trees** \u2014 7 real sorries incl. `bundle := sorry` (representability-gated, out of T9 scope) plus the `descentThroughBirationalSigma`/`albanese_universal_property` assembly. Blueprint DAG is honest: `has_sorry` flags match Lean. `WeilDivisor.lean`'s `PrimeDivisor`/`order` substrate is a live dependency of this leg (`I-0106`), not dead genus-0 weight.",
